article.headline: Wright St. 57, Ill.-Chicago 31
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio -- Todd Brown scored 23 points and had only two fewer field goals than Illinois-Chicago did in Wright State's 57-31 victory on Saturday night. Brown, who also had nine rebounds, hit 9-of-18 shots from the field including 4-of-9 3-pointers. Troy Tabler added 10 points for the Raiders (12-8, 6-3 Horizon League). Scott Vandermeer had 10 points for the Flames (10-9, 3-6), who hit just 11-of-42 shots from the field for 26 percent. The Flames trailed just 34-25 at the 13:26 mark of the second half but the Raiders scored 23 of the game's final 29 points.
